50|$|The Supreme Court of British Columbia {{published}} a Synopsis of <b>Reasons</b> <b>for</b> <b>Judgment</b> which described the general {{nature and the}} outcome of the proceedings. The court ruled that the synopsis was sufficient public disclosure.|$|R
5000|$|Justice Hawco {{stated in}} his <b>Reasons</b> <b>for</b> <b>Judgment,</b> [...] "If I were to place Mr. Ferguson on this ladder of moral culpability, given the facts which the jury must have concluded, {{he would be}} on the very lower rungs." ...|$|R
